HI Jordan,

Here is the past communication from designer to myself. You can see my
brands goals below which I'd say is what I would want in the website as
well.
Also sent the google sheet of the start of the website organization. Have
Audrey to thank for that one, she helped us get the ball rolling.
Eager to help Byron get more organized and hopefully lead to more customers=
.

Thanks!
Kara French
------------------------------




*Hi Kristine, *

Thank you so much for your reply and questions. I enjoy this process and
wish I was as gifted as you at the design and artistic side of things. I
will do my best to answer the questions and hopefully explain tile drainage
a little more so we can play with the right symbols to make a fun logo.


*Typography*
*Which WORD do you want the largest and most prominent =E2=80=9CBluewater=
=E2=80=9D or
=E2=80=9CDrainage=E2=80=9D?*
Bluewater is the main word we want to focus on, and I like how Farm and
Drainage has fit under it in Series #1. I do think I prefer it All Caps as
in series #3 A or B though.



*Slogan*
See other email. I need to know if we=E2=80=99ll be including a tagline on =
one of
the logo versions, since that affects how I line up the bottom of the
elements align. ie lines/icons needs to go above or to the left, so we can
add a tagline later below.
Working on this one. I've been searching the Canadian Trademarks Database
to ensure our potential slogan isn't registered.

Taglines we are playing with but nothing is set yet:

Control the water. Grow the yield.
Where efficiency meets yield.
Results you can farm on.
Groundwork for Better Yields.


*Colours*
Awesome ok- will not use a lighter blue. In some of these I was using the
lighter blue to create the feeling of a flow of water. But I can try it in
another way.
If you need to create dimension- that's fine. I just wanted to focus on 1
or 2 main colours for the business.

*Tiling System Patterns*
You mentioned previously you could send me diagrams of some other field
tiling systems/patterns. And that Clark was an actual pattern example. I=E2=
=80=99m
trying to find more symbolic patterns and elements or videos to help me
come up with ideas. I=E2=80=99ll try to google more of the drainage and til=
ing
aspect of your company to find more ideas and examples. But if you have any
other pictures or youtube video examples that might help .. pls do send, to
help me visualize. Ie how do they dig the pipes in? Perhaps if it digs down
a wedge into the ground, I could do a triangle element slicing down into a
circle.

Tile Drainage Basics:

Also, I've attached a powerpoint that Byron has used when he has presented
to other farmers about the benefits of tile drainage.
You don't have to invest too much time into it but it may help give you the
benefits and reasoning around tile drainage. Slide 5 is Byron's plow - and
has a good picture of one of the shanks and "boots" that rip into the
ground and installs the tile behind it. Here is a better picture of another
plow that shows where it digs into the ground. They first dig a hole with
an excavator, then lower this shank into the hole, and then drive - pulling
shank forward.

<image.png>

You asked for some quick videos- here's 2 you can check out if you want:

https://www.youtube.com/shorts/Rtgzp4ZiuAE - Basic description of tile
drainage

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=3DPFSL23Zo2bI  - Just short video of a tile
plow working in a field


Here's 2 maps of a finished field. It's not a B- but you get the idea.

<image.png>

<image.png>


*Company Name*
*Reading again your full list of services, I am concerned about your new
company name, as it pigeon holes you into Drainage..and does not clearly
represent or speak to the idea you have further services. I know you are
still considering the name. Recalling your original proposed Tag line =E2=
=80=9CFarm
Improvement=E2=80=9D. I wonder if you might consider making your name that?
=E2=80=9CBluewater Farm Improvement=E2=80=9D ? =E2=80=9CBluewater Farm Serv=
ices=E2=80=9D? Hmmmm.*

The name has been registered so we are set on Buewater Farm Drainage. I
tried on this one to have him use his name (Bothwell Farm Drainage) I just
thought it was more unique, and the letters would lend better to a more
unique logo. But he's set on this one. We also have Bluewater Organic Farms
- which we hopefully can connect our logo to in the future. So yes,
Bluewater is the main typography we want to focus on. And I appreciate your
including the grain symbol in the Series #3 and #4 options and wonder if I
shouldn't be so harsh on those symbols. You're right that we should try to
keep this connected to farming angle as well.  I just know I don't want the
token barn.


Ok truth be told I shared with Byron as I need his input on the slogan. We
like 1C, just can't see the B in it. He also likes the 3B icon, if we could
use the lines as a B - maybe rotate 90 degrees clockwise, and somehow mesh
1C and 3B together (but remove the crop for now?). I don't know not a full
B but using tile lines, with the B in mind? I'm worried it's going to look
like any other letter like that (an R or K) so not sure what you can do? I
agree, it doesn't have to be a full B, and you can manipulate the shape to
be a bit hidden.

*Timing*
He is the most chill and flexible person ever. We are just excited to get
this process finally done right!

Let me know if you need anything else! I feel like I've gone a little
overboard on this email =F0=9F=99=82


