,sans-serif;font-size:11pt">
After reviewing the designs, I don=E2=80=99t feel they=E2=80=99re quite hit=
ting the mark yet for what I=E2=80=99m envisioning. A number of the concept=
s feel quite busy, and I=E2=80=99m really aiming for something that is clea=
n, bold, and immediately recognizable.</div>
<div style=3D"font-style:normal;font-variant-caps:normal;font-weight:400;le=
tter-spacing:normal;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;=
word-spacing:0px;text-decoration-line:none;text-decoration-style:solid;text=
-align:left;line-height:1.284;margin:0cm 0cm 8pt;font-family:Verdana,Geneva=
,sans-serif;font-size:11pt">
I=E2=80=99m also finding that some of the agricultural elements (like plant=
s or barn-style cues) feel a bit surface-level rather than meaningfully int=
egrated into the logo. I=E2=80=99d prefer something that more reflects the =
work itself with a subtle references to drainage
 tile, the drainage system or field layout in a simple, refined way. Not cl=
ich=C3=A9 or token agricultural symbols such as the wheat stalk and=C2=A0 a=
 barn.=C2=A0</div>
<div style=3D"font-style:normal;font-variant-caps:normal;font-weight:400;le=
tter-spacing:normal;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;=
word-spacing:0px;text-decoration-line:none;text-decoration-style:solid;text=
-align:left;line-height:1.284;margin:0cm 0cm 8pt;font-family:Verdana,Geneva=
,sans-serif;font-size:11pt">
I do like the direction of the custom =E2=80=9CB=E2=80=9D icon in 1C, but i=
t feels a bit confusing in its current form. The inner negative space tends=
 to draw the eye first and becomes the focal point, while the =E2=80=9CB=E2=
=80=9D (and connection to BFD) is harder to read. It would be great
 to potentially see this concept refined so the letterform is clearer and t=
he negative space supports it rather than competing with it.</div>
